0on%20India%E2%80%99s%20leading%20video%20news%20agency%20ANI%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20tax%20evasion.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20recently%20directed%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20to%20reconsider%20the%20amount%20of%20reward%20to%20be%20given%20to%20a%20person%20who%20informed%20the%20agencies%20about%20alleged%20tax%20evasion%20by%20ANI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20whistleblower%20had%20moved%20the%20top%20court%20alleging%20that%20he%20was%20not%20paid%20his%20legitimate%20reward%20by%20the%20finance%20ministry%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20his%20information%20about%20ANI%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20correct%20and%20which%20forced%20the%20news%20agency%20to%20clear%20its%20tax%20dues.%20The%20appellant%20complained%20that%20he%20had%20informed%20the%20tax%20sleuths%20that%20ANI%20had%20not%20paid%20its%20service%20tax%20dues%20of%20around%20Rs%202.59%20crores.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20information%20was%20used%20to%20send%20a%20non-compliance%20notice%20to%20the%20ANI%2C%20following%20which%20the%20news%20agency%20cleared%20its%20pending%20taxes.%20However%2C%20the%20appellant%20contended%20that%20he%20was%20paid%20only%20Rs%205.50%20lakhs%20as%20a%20reward%20for%20his%20information%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20was%20entitled%20to%20get%20Rs%2051.80%20lakhs%20according%20to%20clause%204.1%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CReward%20to%20Informers%E2%80%9D%20policy%20issued%20by%20the%20revenue%20department%20of%20the%20Union%20finance%20ministry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClause%204.1%20of%20the%20policy%20states%20that%20whistleblowers%20are%20entitled%20to%20get%20up%20to%2020%25%20of%20the%20amount%20of%20tax%20evaded%20and%20fines%20and%20penalties%20imposed%20on%20the%20defaulters.%20The%20appellant%20had%20moved%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20in%202015%20but%20received%20an%20unfavourable%20order%20from%20the%20court.%20He%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20later%2C%20which%20has%20now%20said%20that%20the%20reward%20committee%20did%20not%20apply%20its%20mind%20while%20granting%20the%20award.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fsupreme-court%2Fsupreme-court-centre-reconsider-reward-tax-evasion-by-news-agency-ani-media-pvt-ltd-asian-news-international-233935%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20the%20apex%20court%20also%20directed%20the%20finance%20ministry%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20a%20fresh%20decision%E2%80%9D%20on%20how%20much%20the%20informant%C2%A0%20has%20to%20be%20paid%20as%20a%20reward%20for%20the%20leads%20against%20ANI%20within%20six%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20cited%20that%20there%20were%20no%20reasons%20given%20to%20the%20appellant%20by%20the%20authorities%20for%20restricting%20his%20reward%20money%20to%20Rs%205.50%20lakhs%20instead%20of%2020%25%20as%20stated%20in%20the%20policy.%20It%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20in%202018%20had%20raised%20the%20reward%20money%20for%20the%20appellant%20to%20Rs%209.45%20lakhs%20without%20stating%20any%20reason%20%E2%80%93%20a%20point%20which%20the%20court%20believed%20is%20reflective%20of%20the%20non-application%20of%20mind%20and%20arbitrary%20nature%20of%20the%20way%20the%20reward%20money%20was%20allocated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20social%20media%20users%20highlighted%20ANI%E2%80%99s%20tax%20evasion%20since%20the%20news%20broke%2C%20the%20news%20agency%20issued%20a%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CANI%20Media%20Pvt.%20Ltd.%20(%E2%80%98ANI%E2%80%99)%20has%20been%20a%20multimedia%20news%20agency%20for%20over%20five%20decades.%20In%202010%2C%20ANI%20had%20received%20a%20demand%20from%20the%20appropriate%20authority%20for%20payment%20of%20deficient%20service%20tax.%20This%20demand%20was%20voluntarily%20and%20duly%20complied%20without%20contest%20by%20ANI%20forthwith.%20This%20was%20duly%20accepted%20by%20the%20competent%20authorities%20and%20the%20matter%20stood%20closed.%20ANI%20is%20in%20full%20compliance%20with%20all%20applicable%20laws%20and%20there%20is%20no%20outstanding%20tax%20demand%20against%20it%20as%20on%20date.%20There%20has%20been%20an%20attempt%20to%20mischaracterize%20an%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20unrelated%20proceedings%20where%20ANI%20is%20not%20even%20arrayed%20as%20a%20party.%20Any%20insinuation%20or%20suggestion%20of%20any%20wrongdoing%20is%20mischievous%20and%20defamatory%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690703707000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-whistleblower-ani-tax-dues%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20news%20agency%20ANI%20has%20said%2C%20'There%20has%20been%20an%20attempt%20to%20mischaracterize%20an%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20unrelated%20proceedings%20where%20ANI%20is%20not%20even%20arrayed%20as%20a%20party.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trinity%20Test%20video%3A%20Netizens%20hail%20Nolan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690701434000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102246665%2Cimgsize-40074.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Foppenheimer-netizens-hail-christopher-nolan-after-an-alleged-real-video-of-trinity-test-goes-viral%2Farticleshow%2F102246651.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102246651.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EIn%20Christopher%20Nolan's%20%E2%80%98Oppenheimer%E2%80%99%2C%20Irish%20actor%20Cillian%20Murphy%20(Peaky%20Blinders)%20is%20seen%20as%20%E2%80%98the