org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-66351871.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-66351871.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gig%20Workers'%20First%20Major%20Victory%20in%20India%3A%20Rajasthan%20Leads%20the%20Way%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F22122808%2FZomato_Swiggy_PTI1-1200.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Famit-shah-spins-manipur-tale-on-modis%5C%22%3Ewas%20first%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20The%20India%20Cable%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20times%20of%20crashing%20labour%20rights%2C%20the%20new%20Rajasthan%20Platform-Based%20Gig%20Workers%20(Registration%20and%20Welfare)%20Act%2C%202023%20(or%20RGW%20Act%2C%20as%20I%20will%20be%20referring%20to)%20comes%20up%20as%20a%20breath%20of%20fresh%20air.%C2%A0%20This%20first-of-its-kind%20ground-breaking%20piece%20of%20legislation%20aims%20to%20establish%20a%20welfare%20board%20and%20a%20dedicated%20social%20security%20fund%20for%20platform-based%20gig%20workers%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20bill%20is%20also%20highly%20applaudable%20because%20it%20is%20a%20result%20of%20the%20sheer%20perseverance%20of%20civil%20society%20pressure%20groups%20like%20MKSS%2C%20struggles%20of%20workers%E2%80%99%20unions%20like%20IFAT%20(Indian%20Federation%20of%20App-based%20Transport%20Workers)%20and%20rare%20political%20will%20demonstrated%20by%20the%20Rajasthan%20government%2C%20all%20of%20what%20has%20made%20this%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajasthan%20government%20under%20chief%20minister%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20has%20been%20in%20the%20news%20for%20pioneering%20a%20number%20of%20pro-people%20and%20rights-based%20legislations%20from%20introducing%20the%20Right%20to%20Health%20Bill%20in%202022%2C%20to%20Rajasthan%20Minimum%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Bill%2C%202023%20(upholding%20the%20right%20to%20work)%20to%20this%20RGW%20Bill%202023%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20a%20promised%20allocation%20of%20Rs%20200%20crore%20to%20the%20Gig%20Workers%20Security%20and%20Welfare%20Fund%2C%20interventions%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20help%20the%20Congress%20Party%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Rajasthan%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20polls%202023%20and%20setting%20an%20example%20for%20other%20states%20and%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20Congress%20government%20in%20Karnataka%20announced%20a%20seed%20fund%20of%20Rs%203%2C000%20crore%20for%20comprehensive%20accidental%20and%20life%20insurance%20coverage%20under%20a%20%E2%80%9CGig%20Workers%20Welfare%20Board%E2%80%9D%20for%20Karnataka%20after%20coming%20to%20power%2C%20as%20was%20promised%20in%20their%20recent%20election%20manifesto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20recent%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-publications.bcg.com%2FIndia-Gig-Economy-Report.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20gig%20economy%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20service%20up%20to%2090%20million%20jobs%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20non-farm%20economy%20alone%2C%20transact%20over%20USD%20250%20bn%20in%20volume%20of%20work%2C%20and%20contribute%20an%20incremental%201.25%25%20(approx.)%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20over%20the%20long%20term.%20India%E2%80%99s%20gig%20economy%20workforce%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20contributors%20to%20the%20global%20gig%20workforce.%20This%20clearly%20shows%20the%20exploding%20importance%20of%20platform%2Fgig%20workers%20in%20the%20larger%20political%20economy%20of%20India%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fall-is-not-well-with-indias-gig-economy%5C%22%3EAll%20is%20Not%20Well%20With%20India%E2%80%99s%20Gig%20Economy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gig%20economy%20acts%20like%20a%20net%20for%20millions%20of%20unemployed%20youth%20(and%20elderly)%20to%20join%20this%20low-cost%2C%20low%20investment%20labour%20market%2C%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20subsistence%20and%20%E2%80%9Cflexi-work%E2%80%9D%20offered%20by%20platforms%20like%20Ola%2C%20Uber%2C%20Swiggy%2C%20Zomato%2C%20Urban%20Company%2C%20Porter%2C%20Dunzo%2C%20BlinkIt%2C%20Amazon%20Turks%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20platforms%20call%20themselves%20%E2%80%9Ctech%20aggregators%E2%80%9D%2F%20%E2%80%9Cmediators%E2%80%9D%2F%20%E2%80%9Cfacilitators%E2%80%9D%20and%20not%20employers%20and%20misclassify%20these%20workers%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpartners%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cmini-entrepreneurs%E2%80%9D%20and%20not%20employees%20to%20evade%20all%20possible%20responsibility%20and%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F22122938%2FSwiggy-delivery-waiting_PTI.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F22122938%2FSwiggy-delivery-waiting_PTI.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F22122938%2FSwiggy-delivery-waiting_PTI-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F22122938%2FSwiggy-delivery-waiting_PTI-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-499746%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20even%20though%20many%20factors%20like%20the%20mode%20of%20employment%20arrangements%2C%20payment%20arrangements%2C%20costs%2C%20fairs%2C%20incentives%2C%20penalties%2C%20and%20entry%20into%20and%20exit%20from%20this%20labour%20market%20are%20not%20wholly%20determined%20by%20the%20worker.%20The%20workers%20are%20often%20expected%20to%20obey%20and%20comply%20with%20rules%20and%20conditions%20often%20seen%20in%20formal%20job%20markets%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20wearing%20uniforms%2C%20carrying%20documents%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20and%20also%20adhering%20to%20the%20terms%20and%20targets%20set%20by%20these%20companies.%20However%2C%20the%20fruits%20of%20formal%20employment%20do%20not%20accrue%20to%20them%2C%20such%20as%20decent%20work%2C%20fixed%20working%20hours%20and%20social%20security%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20in%20cases%20of%20accidents%20or%20even%20violence%20at%20work%20as%20reported%20by%20some%20of%20these%20workers%2C%20instead%20of%20offering%20compensation%20or%20support%2C%20many%20of%20these%20companies%20have%20reportedly%20gone%20ahead%20and%20deleted%20the%20databases%20of%20the%20aggrieved%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20context%20that%20the%20RGW%20Act%202023%20is%20a%20historic%20one%20with%20offerings%20like%20registration%20of%20all%20gig%20workers%20(and%20issuing%20unique%20IDs%20to%20each)%2C%20registration%20of%20aggregators%20and%20primary%20employers%3B%20proposed%20monetary%20cess%20(less%20than%202%25%20and%20more%20than%201%25)%20levied%20on%20each%20platform-based%20transaction%2Fduty%20to%20be%20contributed%20to%20the%20social%20security%20fund%20for%20the%20workers%3B%20provision%20of%20social%20security%20benefits%20to%20these%20workers%20(including%20accident%20and%20health%20insurance%2C%20maternity%2C%20gratuity%2C%20pension%2C%20EPF%2C%20ESIC%2C%20scholarships%20in%20consonance%20with%20existing%20schemes%20as%20prescribed)%3B%20grievance%20redressal%20mechanism%20for%20the%20workers%2C%20regular%20consultations%20with%20trade%20unions%20working%20with%20platform%20workers%2C%20provisions%20for%20heavy%20penalties%20(up%20to%20Rs%2050%20lakh)%20on%20non-complying%20aggregators%20and%20employers%2C%20among%20others.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20proposed%20welfare%20board%20is%20to%20comprise%20state%20officials%2C%20representatives%20of%20workers%2C%20aggregators%20and%20civil%20society%2C%20with%20at%20least%20one-third%20of%20the%20nominated%20members%20to%20be%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findia-gig-workers-protests-pil%5C%22%3EInside%20the%20Winter%20of%20Discontent%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20Gig%20Workers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20issues%20being%20raised%20by%20unions%20around%20the%20Act%20are%20that%20no%20portion%20of%20the%20contributions%20to%20the%20fund%20should%20be%20deducted%20from%20the%20workers%E2%80%99%20earnings%20as%20they%20are%20already%20heavily%20distressed.%20Secondly%2C%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20board%20and%20rules%20should%20be%20done%20before%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct%20so%20that%20elections%20and%20the%20results%20do%20not%20stall%20or%20delay%20the%20implementation%20process.%20Other%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20need%20for%20provisions%20on%20basic%20minimum%20earnings%2C%20capping%20of%20commission%20rates%20and%20deductions%20by%20companies%2C%20capping%20of%20maximum%20working%20hours%2C%20stopping%20illegal%20and%20arbitrary%20deactivation%20of%20workers%E2%80%99%20IDs%2C%20data%20transparency%2C%20provisions%20for%20fuel%20and%20other%20inflation-adjusted%20fares%20and%20allowances%20in%20the%20RGW%20Act%20and%20Motor%20Vehicles%20Aggregator%20Rules%202023%20etc.%20should%20be%20considered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20lessons%20of%20success%20and%20failure%20from%20other%20labour%20boards%20(Mathari%20Board%2C%20Construction%20Workers%20Welfare%20Board%2C%20Town%20Vending%20Committees%20under%20Street%20Vending%20Act%202014%20etc.)%20established%20in%20the%20past%20should%20be%20seriously%20studied%20so%20that%20this%20new%20Act%20could%20be%20an%20exemplary%20blueprint%20for%20not%20just%20the%20entire%20gig-force%20of%20India%2C%20but%20also%20for%20over%2050%20crore%20workers%20of%20India%2C%20their%20social%20security%2C%20labour%20rights%20and%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20age%20of%20platform%20capitalism%2C%20with%20skewed%20and%20anti-worker%20algorithms%20operating%20as%20digital%20bosses%2C%20such%20a%20progressive%20law%20could%20possibly%20play%20a%20role%20in%20taming%20these%20bosses%20and%20paving%20the%20way%20to%20imagine%20open-sourced%2C%20worker-owned%20platforms%20and%20digital%20commons%20with%20fairer%20and%20humane%20labour%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20such%20legislation%2C%20if%20implemented%20well%2C%20will%20be%20the%20first%20step%20in%20giving%20a%20dignified%20identity%20and%20recognition%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgig%20worker%E2%80%9D%20who%20can%20claim%20her%2Fhis%20rights%20from%20the%20state%2C%20can%20hold%20the%20platform%20accountable%2C%20will%20have%20a%20representation%20in%20decision-making%2C%20and%20is%20not%20merely%20reduced%20to%20an%20%E2%80%9COla%20driver%E2%80%9D%20or%20a%20%E2%80%9CSwiggy%20delivery%20person%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAkriti%20Bhatia%20is%20the%20Founder%20of%20PAIGAM%20(People%E2%80%99s%20Association%20in%20Grassroots%20Action%20and%20Movements)%2C%20a%20media%20advocacy%20and%20action%20research%20platform.%20She%20has%20submitted%20her%20PhD%20at%20the%20Delhi%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20Department%20of%20Sociology%20and%20specialises%20on%20urban%2C%20labour%20and%20election%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690680641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F22122808%2FZomato_Swiggy_PTI1-1200.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fgig-workers-first-major-victory-in-india-rajasthan-leads-the-way%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I