20north%20Kashmir%20town%20of%20Sopore.%20Amir%20was%20ordered%20to%20appear%20before%20the%20police.%20He%20immediately%20rang%20up%20his%20father%2C%2062-year-old%20Bashir%20Ahmad%2C%20who%20left%20his%20home%20soon%20after%20the%20call%20to%20join%20Amir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20thought%20it%20was%20regarding%20his%20passport%20application%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bashir%20Ahmad%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20upon%20arriving%20before%20the%20police%2C%20the%20father%20was%20ordered%20to%20leave%20while%20Amir%20was%20asked%20to%20stay.%20The%20following%20day%2C%20Amir%20was%20arrested%20and%20bussed%20across%20the%20mountains%20to%20the%20Kot%20Bhalwal%20prison%20complex%20in%20Jammu.%20He%20was%20slapped%20with%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20(PSA)%2C%20the%20Union%20territory%E2%80%99s%20strict%20preventive%20detention%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20PSA%20dossier%2C%20which%20lists%20out%20the%20grounds%20of%20detention%2C%20accuses%20Amir%20of%20being%20associated%20with%20the%20Pakistan-based%20terrorist%20group%20Lashkar-e-Tayyaba%20(LeT)%2C%20feeding%20and%20sheltering%20terrorists%2C%20and%20using%20encrypted%20communication%20tools%20to%20avoid%20detection.%20It%20also%20charges%20him%20with%20%E2%80%9Caggressively%E2%80%9D%20campaigning%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20terrorist%20group%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26120758%2FIMG_6130_1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26120758%2FIMG_6130_1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26120758%2FIMG_6130_1-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26120758%2FIMG_6130_1-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665158%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAmir%20Bashir%20War%E2%80%99s%20father%20shows%20a%20picture%20of%20his%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%2C%20however%2C%20strongly%20contested%20this%20and%20filed%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20(h%2Fc)%20petition%20at%20the%20Jammu%2C%20Kashmir%20%26amp%3B%20Ladakh%20(JK%26amp%3BL)%20high%20court%20last%20year%2C%20for%20getting%20the%20PSA%20case%20against%20Amir%20quashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20FIR%20registered%20against%20the%2029-year-old%20detainee%2C%20something%20his%20lawyer%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%20could%20help%20get%20his%20detention%20nullified.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20arguing%20that%20the%20detention%20is%20based%20on%20vague%20grounds%20and%20not%20having%20an%20FIR%20is%20in%20support%20of%20our%20argument%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bashir%20Tak%2C%20the%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20case%20has%20come%20up%20for%20hearing%20only%20once%20over%20the%20past%20six%20months%20despite%20it%20figuring%20in%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%99cause%20list%E2%80%99%20on%20seven%20occasions%20since.*%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmir%20is%20not%20the%20only%20PSA%20detenu%20to%20find%20himself%20facing%20this%20predicament.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20families%20who%20have%20had%20their%20loved%20ones%20detained%20under%20the%20Act%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%20lawyers%20who%20are%20fighting%20these%20matters.%20All%20of%20them%20unanimously%20claim%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Clack%20of%20hearing%E2%80%9D%20in%20cases%20pertaining%20to%20detention%20was%20becoming%20a%20%E2%80%9Cregular%20affair%E2%80%9D%20especially%20after%20the%20former%20state%E2%80%99s%20special%20constitutional%20status%20was%20revoked%20in%202019.%20The%20lawyers%20shared%20concerns%20over%20what%20they%20described%20as%20detention%20cases%20being%20pushed%20to%20the%20tail-end%20of%20the%20daily%20cause%20lists%20so%20that%20by%20the%20time%20their%20turn%20arrives%2C%20the%20clocks%20strike%20past%204%20pm%20and%20the%20courts%20call%20it%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%209%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20visited%20the%20high%20court%20complex%20in%20Srinagar%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20various%20families%20who%20were%20there%20to%20attend%20the%20day%E2%80%99s%20proceedings%20as%20the%20cases%20of%20their%20imprisoned%20relatives%20were%20scheduled%20for%20hearing.%20Among%20them%20was%20Saima%20Manzoor%20from%20the%20Kulgam%20district%20of%20south%20Kashmir.%20Her%2024-year-old%20brother%2C%20Irfan%20Manzoor%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20security%20forces%20in%20February%202022%20from%20his%20store%20in%20Mirhama%20village%20where%20he%20sold%20garments.%20His%20family%20said%20he%20was%20lodged%20in%20different%20prisons%20across%20the%20Valley%20before%20being%20flown%20to%20the%20Bareilly%20central%20jail%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpsa-detentions-kashmir%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20Continues%20to%20Haunt%20Kashmir%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20father%20Manzoor%20Ahmad%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20remember%20the%20last%20time%20the%20case%20had%20come%20up%20for%20hearing%20(high%20court%20documents%20show%20it%20was%20on%20March%207%20this%20year)%20but%20whenever%20it%20was%20listed%2C%20the%20family%20would%20travel%2070%20kms%20to%20Srinagar%20to%20attend%20the%20court%20proceedings%20which%20were%20always%20few%20and%20far%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20come%20here%20each%20time%20his%20case%20is%20listed%20for%20hearing%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20wait%20for%20the%20whole%20day%2C%20sometimes%20without%20food%2C%20only%20to%20be%20informed%20that%20the%20judges%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20hear%20the%20case.%20They%20take%20up%20supplementary%20and%20regular%20cases%20and%20those%20that%20have%20come%20from%20the%20final%20hearing%20are%20not%20prioritised.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManzoor%E2%80%99s%20case%20was%20scheduled%20in%20the%20daily%20cause-list%2025%20times%20since%20May%20last%20year%20but%20orders%20have%20been%20passed%20only%20on%20five%20occasions%2C%20of%20which%20four%20pertain%20only%20to%20the%20court%20instructing%20the%20respondents%20(i.e.%20J%26amp%3BK%20UT)%20to%20file%20detention%20records.%20On%20June%209%2C%20Manzoor%E2%80%99s%20case%20was%20listed%20104%20on%20the%20serial%20list.%20His%20family%20had%20already%20resigned%20itself%20to%20the%20fct%20that%20it%20will%20not%20be%20heard.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20to%20leave%20in%20the%20evening%2C%E2%80%9D%20Manzoor%20Ahmad%20later%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20over%20a%20phone%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20PSA%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJ%26amp%3BK%20Public%20Safety%20Act%201978%20is%20a%20controversial%20preventive%20detention%20law%20that%20allows%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20to%20detain%20individuals%20pre-emptively%20for%20six%20months%20and%20prolong%20their%20detention%20for%20up%20to%20two%20years%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20threat%20the%20authorities%20believe%20they%20could%20pose%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmaintenance%20of%20law%20and%20order%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadvisory-board-detention-orders-jk-systematically-subjugated%5C%22%3EAdvisory%20Board%20Examining%20Detention%20Orders%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%98Systematically%20Subjugated%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20mechanism%20to%20get%20bail%20under%20PSA.%20The%20cases%20are%20moved%20to%20an%20advisory%20board%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20whose%20members%20are%20selected%20by%20the%20administration%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20which%20determines%20whether%20they%20are%20filed%20on%20reasonable%20grounds.%20If%20the%20case%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20meet%20the%20board%E2%80%99s%20admissibility%20test%2C%20it%20is%20revoked.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadvisory-board-detention-orders-jk-systematically-subjugated%5C%22%3EOfficial%20documents%3C%2Fa%3E%20obtained%20by%20legal%20researchers%20in%202018%20revealed%20that%20for%202016-17%2C%20only%200.6%25%20of%20PSA%20cases%20by%20the%20authorities%20failed%20to%20get%20past%20the%20board.%20In%20the%20remaining%2099.4%25%20of%20cases%2C%20involving%20998%20persons%2C%20the%20board%20confirmed%20the%20detention%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20option%20left%20for%20the%20families%20of%20the%20detained%20persons%20is%20to%20then%20appeal%20against%20their%20incarceration%20by%20filing%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20petition%20in%20the%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20PSA%20is%20analogous%20to%20the%20National%20Security%20Act%2C%201980%20(a%20federal%20law)%2C%20the%20latter%20is%20less%20severe%20because%20it%20allows%20a%20person%20to%20be%20detained%20for%20a%20maximum%20of%2012%20months%20as%20opposed%20to%20two%20years%20in%20the%20case%20of%20PSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20Union%20government%20rammed%20hundreds%20of%20central%20laws%20through%20the%20Union%20territory%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20reading%20down%20Article%20370%20%E2%80%94%20under%20whose%20aegis%20the%20PSA%20was%20first%20legislated%20%E2%80%94%20it%20did%20not%20substitute%20the%20PSA%20with%20NSA.%20Instead%2C%20it%20retained%20the%20law%20within%20the%20legal%20framework%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%2C%20something%20that%20human%20rights%20groups%20such%20as%20Amnesty%20International%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Famnesty-international-srinagar-press-briefing-detentions%5C%22%3Ehave%20slammed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Famnesty-international-srinagar-press-briefing-detentions%5C%22%3EExplainer%3A%20How%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20Has%20Been%20(Mis)used%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowing%20number%20of%20habeas%20corpus%20appeals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20high%20court%20data%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20petitions%20challenging%20detention%20under%20PSA%20appeared%20to%20have%20spiked%20sharply%20last%20year.%20In%202019%2C%20when%20Article%20370%20provisions%20were%20scrapped%20and%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20state%20bifurcated%2C%20the%20high%20court%20received%20507%20such%20pleas.%20In%20the%20following%20years%2C%20the%20figures%20stood%20at%20203%20(in%202020)%2C%20327%20(in%202021)%2C%20and%20841%20(in%202022)%20respectively%2C%20signifying%20a%20sharp%20increase.%20This%20year%20so%20far%20the%20high%20court%20has%20received%20266%20petitions%20out%20of%20which%20only%2016%20have%20been%20disposed%20of%20while%20250%20are%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20lawyers%20who%20fight%20PSA%20cases%20at%20the%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court%2C%20two%20significant%20changes%20that%20judicial%20authorities%20have%20implemented%20hold%20the%20key%20to%20understanding%20such%20a%20spike.%20On%20April%2017%2C%202019%2C%20three%20months%20before%20Article%20370%20was%20scrapped%2C%20an%20order%20issued%20under%20the%20aegis%20of%20the%20registrar%20general%20at%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20high%20court%20sought%20to%20make%20rationalisation%20of%20nomenclature%20and%20categorisation%20of%20cases%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20scientific%20and%20in%20tune%20with%20nomenclature%20prevalent%20in%20other%20high%20courts%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122032%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T121724.342.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122032%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T121724.342.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122032%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T121724.342-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122032%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T121724.342-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665169%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20J%26amp%3BK%20High%20Court%20Registrar%20General%E2%80%99s%20April%2017%2C%202019%20notices%20along%20with%20its%20Annexures%20which%20affirm%20the%20change%20of%20nomenclature%20from%20Habeas%20Corpus%20to%20WP%20(Crl).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20annexure%20accompanying%20the%20document%2C%20the%20new%20nomenclature%20for%20habeas%20corpus%20cases%20has%20been%20changed%20to%20Writ%20Petition%20Criminal%2C%20WP%20(Crl).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20slow%20grind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20lawyers%2C%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20high%20court%20followed%20a%20particular%20convention%20pursuant%20to%20which%20habeas%20corpus%20pleas%20were%20preferentially%20prioritised%20and%20heard%20expeditiously.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20what%20we%20call%20%E2%80%98case%20flow%20management%20rules%E2%80%99%20at%20the%20high%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20one%20senior%20lawyer%20pleading%20anonymity.%20%E2%80%9CUnder%20those%20rules%2C%20liberty%20matters%20were%20required%20to%20be%20decided%20within%2015%20days.%20Although%20no%20PSA%20cases%20were%20decided%20within%2015%20days%2C%20at%20least%20disposal%20used%20to%20happen%20in%20a%20few%20months%E2%80%99%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20after%20the%20April%202019%20notification%2C%20habeas%20petitions%20were%20being%20treated%20on%20par%20with%20what%20he%20termed%20%E2%80%98routine%20matters%E2%80%99%20and%20therefore%20not%20prioritised%20in%20ways%20in%20which%20they%20were%20previously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court%20circular%20dated%20April%207%2C%202023%2C%20stipulates%20the%20scheduling%20of%20cases%20pending%20%E2%80%9Cabove%20ten%20years%E2%80%9D%20on%20Tuesdays%20and%20Thursdays.%20The%20circular%2C%20like%20the%20previous%20one%2C%20is%20also%20prefaced%20with%20good%20intentions.%20It%20mentions%20that%20the%20new%20rules%20have%20been%20framed%20to%20%E2%80%9Creduce%20arrears%20of%20pendency%20cases%E2%80%9D.%20It%20designates%20these%20two%20days%20exclusively%20for%20%E2%80%98final%20hearing%E2%80%99%20during%20which%20%E2%80%9Cno%20other%20non-hearing%20matter%20will%20be%20taken%20unless%20permitted%20by%20the%20chief%20justice%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122841%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T122805.560.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122841%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T122805.560.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122841%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T122805.560-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26122841%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-26T122805.560-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665174%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOn%20the%20right%2C%20the%20JK%26amp%3BL%20High%20Court%20Registrar%20General%E2%80%99s%20notice%20which%20stipulates%20scheduling%20the%20cases%20%E2%80%9Cabove%20ten%20years%E2%80%9D%20on%20Tuesdays%20and%20Thursdays.%20On%20the%20left%2C%20the%20Registrar%20General%E2%80%99s%20notice%20confirming%20that%20habeas%20corpus%20petitions%20shall%20be%20listed%20on%20Mondays%2C%20Wednesdays%20and%20Fridays%20until%20further%20order%20to%20keep%20Tuesdays%2C%20Thursdays%20to%20be%20exclusive%20hearing%20days%20for%20old%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20days%20later%2C%20on%20April%2011%2C%20yet%20another%20communication%20by%20the%20registrar%20general%2C%20citing%20instructions%20by%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court%2C%20ordered%20that%20%E2%80%9Chabeas%20corpus%20petitions%20shall%20be%20listed%20on%20Mondays%2C%20Wednesdays%2C%20and%20Fridays%20until%20further%20order%20to%20keep%20Tuesdays%2C%20Thursdays%20to%20be%20exclusive%20hearing%20days%20for%20old%20matters%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EG.N.%20Shaheen%2C%20a%20senior%20lawyer%20and%20spokesperson%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%20High%20Court%20Bar%20Association%2C%20said%20that%20these%20notices%20have%20led%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20cases%20filed%20under%20%E2%80%98orders%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98admissions%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98before-notice%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98after-notice%E2%80%99%20categories%20cram%20the%20cause-list%20on%20the%20remaining%20three%20work%20days%20in%20the%20week%20as%20a%20result%20of%20which%20cases%20concerning%20personal%20liberty%20find%20themselves%20on%20the%20tail-end.%20%E2%80%9CDetention%20matters%20are%20otherwise%20a%20priority%20across%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Decide%20the%20cases%20on%20merits%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wait%20has%20been%20grueling%20for%20Idrees%20Dar%20(30)%2C%20a%20labourer%20from%20the%20south%20Kashmir%20district%20of%20Kulgam.%20His%2019-year-old%20brother%20Mohammad%20Ilyas%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20police%20on%20the%20apprehension%20that%20he%20was%20likely%20to%20join%20a%20militant%20faction.%20His%20PSA%20document%20issued%20by%20the%20Kulgam%20dstrict%20magistrate%2C%20accuses%20him%20of%20being%20involved%20in%20stone-throwing%20protests%20in%20September%202021%20when%20demonstrations%20had%20erupted%20following%20the%20demise%20of%20Hurriyat%20leader%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhow-syed-ali-shah-geelanis-body-was-taken-from-his-family-buried-in-haste%5C%22%3ESyed%20Ali%20Shah%20Geelani%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ilyas%20was%20arrested%20in%20April%202022%2C%20Dar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20first%20lodged%20in%20Kot%20Bhalwal%20jail%20in%20Jammu%20before%20being%20relocated%20to%20a%20Haryana%20jail%20that%20August.%20His%20case%20was%20listed%2024%20times%20but%20the%20court%20documents%20show%20only%20three%20orders.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20approached%20court%20but%20every%20time%20the%20case%20is%20listed%2C%20it%20hovers%20around%20serial%20numbers%20120%2C%20130%2C%20or%20125.%20Our%20turn%20never%20comes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20occasion%20when%20judges%20took%20up%20Ilyas%E2%80%99s%20petition%20was%20on%20March%2031%20this%20year.%20%E2%80%9CI%20appear%20at%20the%20court%20on%20hearing%20days%20dutifully%2C%E2%80%9D%20Idrees%20says.%20%E2%80%9CI%20just%20pray%20that%20the%20judges%20take%20steps%20that%20expedite%20the%20hearing%20process.%20I%20am%20not%20asking%20for%20amnesty.%20The%20case%20should%20be%20decided%20on%20merits.%20But%20at%20least%20they%20need%20to%20hear%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHabeas%20corpus%20is%20an%20overriding%20priority%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20who%20spoke%20to%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20this%20story%20said%20that%20although%20the%20change%20in%20nomenclature%20to%20WP%20(Crl)%20was%20not%20of%20much%20significance%2C%20it%20is%20unfortunate%20that%20this%20has%20led%20to%20the%20sidelining%20of%20PSA%20cases.%20%E2%80%9CA%20request%20has%20been%20pending%20with%20some%20high%20courts%20to%20have%20some%20uniformity%20in%20nomenclature%20so%20that%20data%20of%20cases%20can%20be%20easily%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20computer%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Justice%20Madan.%20B.%20Lokur%2C%20a%20leading%20Indian%20jurist%20and%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Lokur%20said%20that%20every%20high%20court%20gave%20priority%20to%20the%20habeas%20petitions%20because%20the%20detention%20is%20without%20trial.%20And%20this%20has%20been%20the%20practice%20in%20all%20democracies.%20%E2%80%9CSir%20Alfred%20Denning%20%5Ban%20English%20lawyer%20and%20judge%5D%20in%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsocialsciences.exeter.ac.uk%2Fmedia%2Funiversityofexeter%2Fschoolofhumanitiesandsocialsciences%2Flaw%2Fpdfs%2FFreedom_Under_the_Law_1.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Hamlyn%20Lectures%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20in%201949%20says%20that%20all%20other%20work%20stops%20when%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20petition%20is%20mentioned%20for%20listing.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20terrible%20that%20cases%20are%20not%20being%20taken%20up.%20Multiple%20adjournments%20is%20totally%20unacceptable.%20The%20matter%20should%20be%20taken%20up%20with%20the%20chief%20justice%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Justice%20Lokur%20added%20that%20habeas%20petitions%20usually%20do%20not%20take%20long%20to%20decide.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20if%20they%20are%20taken%20up%2C%20it%20will%20not%20unduly%20disturb%20the%20list%20of%20cases%20for%20the%20day.%20Even%20if%20it%20does%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20matter%20because%20of%20the%20importance%20and%20urgency%20in%20hearing%20%5Bthese%5D%20petitions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaheen%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20members%20of%20the%20Bar%20Association%20had%20approached%20the%20present%20chief%20of%20the%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20N.%20Kotiswar%20Singh%2C%20regarding%20this%20matter.%20%E2%80%9COn%20behalf%20of%20the%20association%2C%20we%20requested%20the%20hon%E2%80%99ble%20chief%20justice%20to%20devise%20a%20mechanism%20in%20light%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20orders%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shaheen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20his%20personal%20frustration%20with%20the%20infrequent%20hearings%2C%20Shaheen%20said%20that%20he%20gets%20tens%20of%20phone%20calls%20every%20day%20from%20relatives%20of%20detainees.%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20hearings%20are%20few%20and%20far%20between%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20interventions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20parsed%20through%20more%20recent%20official%20communications%20pertaining%20to%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20high%20court%20which%20reveals%20express%20efforts%20to%20get%20such%20cases%20expedited.%20What%20could%20not%20be%20established%2C%20however%2C%20is%20whether%20these%20interventions%20came%20as%20a%20response%20to%20the%20growing%20clamour%20over%20the%20issue%20of%20fewer%20hearings%20in%20habeas%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%207%2C%20the%20Twitter%20account%20of%20a%20Kashmiri%20lawyer%20reporting%20proceedings%20from%20the%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court%20quoted%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Dhar%20sharing%20concerns%20with%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%E2%80%99s%20additional%20advocate%20general%20over%20habeas%20matters%20not%20being%20taken%20up%20in%20his%20court%20and%20adding%20directions%20that%20such%20petitions%20must%20be%20takne%20up%20before%20his%20court%20at%203%3A30%20pm%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20in%20a%20notification%20dated%20April%2026%20this%20year%2C%20the%20registrar%20general%20rolled%20out%20a%20new%20roster%20valid%20for%20a%20period%20between%20May%201%20and%20June%2017.%20Appended%20to%20the%20circular%20were%20a%20series%20of%20notes%2C%20one%20of%20which%20directs%20the%20judicial%20benches%20to%20hear%20cases%20related%20to%20personal%20liberty%20on%20priority.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20listed%20matters%20related%20to%20personal%20liberties%20are%20not%20taken%20up%20for%20any%20reason%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20day%20in%20that%20event%20these%20matters%20shall%20be%20taken%20up%20by%20the%20concerned%20benches%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20post-lunch%20session%20as%20per%20the%20convenience%20of%20the%20concerned%20roster%20bench%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20507px)%2085vw%2C%20507px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26123102%2FIMG_6257.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22507%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26123102%2FIMG_6257.jpg%20785w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26123102%2FIMG_6257-196x300.jpg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26123102%2FIMG_6257-670x1024.jpg%20670w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665176%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22775%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20copy%20of%20the%20fresh%20roster%20valid%20between%20July%2024%20and%20July%2029%20at%20JK%26amp%3BL%20High%20Court%20which%20reiterates%20%E2%80%98Note%208%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20previous%20roster%20laying%20down%20guidelines%20that%20if%20the%20listed%20matters%20related%20to%20personal%20liberties%20are%20not%20taken%20up%20for%20any%20reason%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20day%20in%20that%20event%20these%20matters%20shall%20be%20taken%20up%20by%20the%20concerned%20benches%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20post-lunch%20session%20as%20per%20the%20convenience%20of%20the%20concerned%20roster%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fresh%20roster%20valid%20between%20July%2024%20and%20July%2029%20also%20reiterates%20these%20instructions.%20Yet%20the%20families%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20said%20it%20has%20hardly%20improved%20things%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyers%20fighting%20PSA%20cases%20had%20a%20bleak%20impression%20to%20share.%20%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20some%20of%20my%20cases%20figured%20at%20serials%20133%20and%20135%20on%20the%20list.%20Yesterday%2C%20one%20case%20was%20at%20serial%20244%20yesterday%2C%20another%20at%20256%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bashir%20Tak%2C%20the%20lawyer%20at%20JK%26amp%3BL%20court%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20interview.%20%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20was%20no%20chance%20a%20case%20placed%20at%20such%20a%20farthest%20end%20will%20be%20heard.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20son%E2%80%99s%20case%20was%20listed%20for%20hearing%20on%20the%2010th%20and%2021st%20of%20July%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bashir%20Ahmad%2C%20Amir%E2%80%99s%20father%20said.%20%E2%80%9COn%20both%20these%20dates%2C%20the%20case%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20heard%20even%20though%20he%20was%20on%20serial%2059%20(general%20category)%20and%20on%20serial%2011%20(final%20hearing)%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20hon%E2%80%99ble%20judge%2C%20however%2C%20did%20take%20up%20two%20other%20cases%2C%20one%20of%20which%20was%20quashed%20and%20another%20reserved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98PSA%20revocation%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20amount%20to%20being%20innocent%E2%80%99%20says%20police%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20officials%20who%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20that%20getting%20released%20from%20the%20PSA%20detention%20does%20not%20imply%20that%20the%20detainee%20is%20%E2%80%98innocent%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20claims%20the%20state%20makes%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20officer%20who%20spoke%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20cited%20the%20case%20of%20Lashkar-e-Toiba%E2%80%99s%20Sajjad%20Tantray%20who%20was%20killed%20in%20November%20last%20year.%20%E2%80%9CTantray%20was%20initially%20detained%20under%20the%20PSA%20in%202019.%20After%20getting%20released%2C%20he%20was%20found%20to%20be%20responsible%20for%20attacking%20two%20migrant%20labourers%20in%20Bijbehara%20in%20south%20Kashmir%20last%20year.%20Similarly%2C%20we%20had%20cases%20of%20terrorists%20like%20Zubair%20Turray%20who%20too%20were%20released%20from%20their%20PSA%20detentions%20before%20they%20joined%20terrorism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20perhaps%20for%20this%20reason%20that%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20has%20in%20recent%20times%20started%20training%20sessions%20so%20that%20officers%20are%20well-equipped%20to%20prepare%20more%20foolproof%20dossiers%20that%20are%20not%20quashed%20in%20the%20courts%20on%20technical%20grounds.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fwith-psa-detentions-getting-quashed-revoked-how-jk-cops-are-trying-make-tighter-cases%2F1377980%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20in%202022%20improved%20their%20tally%20of%20successfully%20seeing%20PSA%20cases%20through%20judicial%20scrutiny.%20The%20nullification%20of%20PSAs%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20high%20court%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20came%20down%20from%2081%20(out%20of%20134%20detentions)%20in%202020%20to%20just%2049%20(out%20of%20749)%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20officer%20speaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20drew%20attention%20to%20what%20he%20called%20the%20decimation%20of%20%E2%80%9Corganised%20militant%20recruitment%E2%80%9D%20which%20has%20led%20to%20a%20change%20in%20the%20ways%20militancy%20is%20being%20operationalised%20in%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%20result%20of%20which%20the%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20are%20increasingly%20relying%20on%20the%20combined%20strength%20of%20PSA%20and%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA)%20to%20keep%20the%20%E2%80%9Cknown%20offenders%20out%20of%20circulation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMilitancy%20has%20turned%20more%20underground.%20The%20recruiters%20make%20careful%20assessments%20of%20who%20they%20should%20enlist%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20officer%20said%20that%20recruiters%20reached%20them%20individually%20through%20encrypted%20chat%20applications.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20networks%20are%20widespread%20but%20the%20work%20apportioned%20to%20every%20next%20person%20down%20the%20chain%20is%20minimal.%20One%20may%20argue%20in%20court%20that%20merely%20providing%20a%20tiffin%20box%20or%20ferrying%20a%20bag%20from%20one%20place%20to%20another%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20amount%20to%20a%20big%20offence.%20But%20we%20have%20to%20look%20at%20the%20whole%20picture.%20These%20individuals%20are%20small%20nuts%20and%20bolts%20of%20the%20same%20apparatus%20that%20mechanises%20the%20bigger%20operation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CCourts%20will%20obviously%20see%20things%20through%20principles%20of%20natural%20justice.%20But%20for%20us%2C%20it%20is%20the%20question%20of%20liability%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20officer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20regular%20cases%20are%20not%20filed%20against%20detainees%20before%20they%20are%20placed%20in%20detention%20under%20the%20PSA%20implicitly%20means%20that%20the%20police%20know%20the%20evidence%20they%20have%20of%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20militancy%20or%20the%20commission%20of%20a%20crime%20likely%20won%E2%80%99t%20hold%20up%20in%20an%20actual%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20review%20of%20the%20PSA%20cases%20being%20quashed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20reviewed%2013%20PSA%20cases%20that%20the%20JK%26amp%3BL%20high%20court%20quashed%20in%20the%20year%202023.%20The%20reasons%20offered%20for%20quashing%20these%20detention%20orders%20show%20that%20despite%20the%20seriousness%20of%20offences%20imputed%20to%20the%20detainees%2C%20PSA%20orders%20end%20up%20being%20invalidated%20because%20the%20plaintiff%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20were%20able%20to%20prove%20that%20the%20detaining%20authority%20%E2%80%93%20which%20in%20the%20case%20of%20this%20law%20are%20the%20district%20magistrates%20(DMs)%20acting%20upon%20dossiers%20submitted%20by%20superintendents%20of%20police%20(SPs)%20or%20higher-ranked%20officers%20%E2%80%93%20did%20not%20apply%20their%20mind%20while%20authorising%20the%20detention%2C%20or%20that%20the%20respondents%20(the%20Union%20territory%20of%20J%26amp%3BK)%2C%20did%20not%20supply%20the%20detainees%20with%20the%20grounds%20of%20detention%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20which%20they%20could%20have%20appealed%20against%20their%20internment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20cases%20of%20Abid%20Hussain%20Ganie%20from%20Anantnag%2C%20Naseer%20Ahmad%20Dar%20from%20Ganderbal%2C%20Waseem%20Ahmad%20Pandith%20from%20Pulwama%2C%20Javeed%20Lone%20from%20Bandipora%2C%20Rouf%20Mushtaq%20Najar%20of%20Shopian%20and%20Ghulam%20Ahmad%20Waza%20of%20Bandipora%2C%20the%20judges%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20is%20a%20mismatch%20between%20detention%20record%20produced%20by%20counsel%20(which%20had%20no%20copies%20of%20FIR)%20and%20submissions%20made%20by%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%20(which%20gave%20reference%20to%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20FIRs.)%20On%20the%20basis%20of%20this%2C%20the%20judges%20determined%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20failure%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20detaining%20authority%20to%20supply%20the%20material%20relied%20%5Bon%5D%20at%20the%20time%20of%20making%20the%20detention%20order%20to%20the%20detenu%20renders%20the%20detention%20order%20illegal%20and%20unsustainable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Ganie%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20the%20court%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9CSurprisingly%2C%20when%20no%20FIR%20is%20shown%20to%20have%20been%20registered%20against%20the%20petitioner%2C%20then%20how%20come%2027%20leaves%20of%20FIR%2C%20etc.%2C%20have%20been%20provided%20to%20him%3F%20This%20exhibits%20total%20non-application%20of%20mind%20and%20overzealousness%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20detaining%20authority%2C%20which%20casts%20serious%20doubt%20about%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20receipt.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20case%2C%20while%20rescinding%20the%20PSA%20orders%20against%20Zahoor%20Ahmad%20Sheikh%20of%20Beerwah%20and%20Umar%20Rashid%20Ganie%20of%20Anantnag%2C%20the%20judges%20noted%20that%20the%20dossier%20of%20the%20SSP%20and%20the%20detention%20order%20of%20the%20DM%20are%20identical%20copies%20of%20each%20other%20and%20that%20this%20indicated%20the%20detaining%20authority%20did%20not%20exercise%20its%20own%20mind%2C%20which%20is%20an%20important%20prerequisite%20to%20ensure%20that%20a%20PSA%20order%20survives%20judicial%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20cases%20of%20Umair%20Mushtaq%20Rather%20from%20Kulgam%2C%20Shafayat%20Amin%20Shah%20from%20Shopian%2C%20and%20Molvi%20Muhammad%20Amin%20Pala%20from%20Anantnag%2C%20the%20court%20observed%20that%20material%20relied%20upon%20by%20the%20detaining%20authority%20was%20not%20furnished%20to%20the%20detainees%20and%20as%20such%20made%20their%20PSA%20%E2%80%9Cunsustainable%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20quashing%20the%20PSA%20order%20against%20journalist%20and%20editor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffahad-shah-public-safety-act-jammu-kashmir-high-court%5C%22%3EFahad%20Shah%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20one%20Feroz%20Zargar%20from%20Kulgam%2C%20the%20judges%20noted%20that%20the%20detaining%20authority%20cannot%20use%20both%20expressions%20%E2%80%9Cprejudicial%20to%20maintenance%20of%20public%20order%E2%80%9D%20as%20well%20as%20%E2%80%9Cprejudicial%20to%20security%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%9D%20as%20they%20have%20different%20connotations%20and%20are%20demarcated%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20gravity%20and%20cannot%20be%20used%20simultaneously%20which%20proves%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdetaining%20authority%20has%20not%20applied%20its%20mind%20while%20passing%20the%20order%20of%20detention.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E*When%20this%20correspondent%20was%20still%20working%20on%20this%20story%2C%20A%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Emir%E2%8