%20modes%20of%20being%2C%20where%20the%20reference%20points%20for%20our%20existence%20become%20our%20neighbours%20or%20peers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20we%20do%20at%20least%20as%20well%20as%20them%2C%20we%20are%20relatively%20satisfied%3B%20otherwise%2C%20not.%20In%20short%2C%20we%20try%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20Joneses.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20215px)%2085vw%2C%20215px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27195833%2FJean-Jacques-Rousseau-215x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22215%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27195833%2FJean-Jacques-Rousseau-215x300.jpg%20215w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27195833%2FJean-Jacques-Rousseau-735x1024.jpg%20735w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27195833%2FJean-Jacques-Rousseau.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665514%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20painting%20of%20Rousseau.%20Photo%3A%20Maurice%20Quentin%20de%20La%20Tour%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20Public%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELet%20us%20turn%20to%20Rousseau%2C%20a%20Swiss%20thinker%20of%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20to%20see%20the%20origins%20of%20such%20impulses%20in%20us.%20He%20had%20a%20term%20for%20it%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamour%20propre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Roughly%20translated%20from%20French%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamour%20propre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20means%20pride%2C%20conceit%20or%20vanity.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPropre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20means%20oneself%20in%20consideration%20with%20others.%20So%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamour%20propre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20kind%20of%20self-love%20that%20depends%20upon%20the%20opinions%20of%20others%20about%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20distinguished%20it%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamour%20de%20soi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20self-love%20proper%20without%20regard%20to%20others%E2%80%99%20opinions.%20He%20felt%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amour%20de%20soi%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eor%20love%20of%20oneself%2C%20was%20a%20natural%20sentiment.%20It%20predates%20the%20formation%20of%20society%20and%20makes%20us%20strive%20to%20preserve%20ourselves%20and%20our%20interests%20by%20tending%20to%20our%20biological%20needs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGuided%20by%20reason%20and%20modified%20by%20pity%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamour%20de%20soi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20produces%20humanity%2C%20virtue%2C%20empathy%20and%20compassion.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmour%20de%20soi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20also%20resists%20the%20invasion%20or%20encroachment%20by%20others%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20self-preservation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmour%20propre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20an%20altogether%20different%20sentiment%20and%20not%20natural%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20self.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmour%20propre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20makes%20us%20value%20ourselves%20more%20than%20anyone%20else%20and%20inspires%20not%20only%20the%20desire%20to%20be%20recognised%2C%20respected%20and%20esteemed%20by%20others%2C%20but%20also%20all%20the%20evils%20that%20beset%20society%2C%20such%20as%20dependence%2C%20dissimulation%2C%20deception%2C%20oppression%20and%20domination.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20thinkers%20like%20Plato%20and%20Hobbes%20saw%20a%20version%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamour%20propre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20being%20natural%20to%20man.%20Plato%20saw%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ethumos%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(spiritedness)%20as%20one%20of%20the%20three%20constituents%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20soul%2C%20the%20other%20two%20being%20appetitive%20and%20rational.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHobbes%20thought%20that%20men%20even%20in%20the%20state%20of%20nature%20(that%20is%2C%20the%20state%20man%20was%20in%20prior%20to%20the%20formation%20of%20society%20%E2%80%93%20a%20speculative%20construct)%20were%20affected%20by%20considerations%20of%20pride%20or%20vainglory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20233px)%2085vw%2C%20233px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27200157%2FHobbes-215x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22233%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27200157%2FHobbes-215x300.jpg%20215w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27200157%2FHobbes-735x1024.jpg%20735w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27200157%2FHobbes.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665515%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22325%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20engraving%20of%20the%2017th-century%20English%20philosopher%20Thomas%20Hobbes.%20Photo%3A%20William%20Faithorne%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20BY-4.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERousseau%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20thinks%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamour%20propre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20sentiment%20that%20we%20acquire%20only%20once%20we%20enter%20society%20in%20one%20way%20or%20another.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERousseau%20speculates%20that%20in%20the%20state%20of%20nature%2C%20men%20wandered%20solitarily%2C%20fulfilling%20their%20biological%20needs%20from%20nature%20and%20not%20seeing%20any%20need%20for%20association%20with%20others.%20Sexual%20relations%20were%20sporadic%20and%20temporary%2C%20and%20families%20did%20not%20coalesce.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20when%20men%20began%20to%20see%20advantages%20to%20hunting%20in%20groups%2C%20they%20began%20to%20associate%20with%20one%20another.%20Then%20settled%20communities%20formed.%20This%20led%20one%20to%20become%20conscious%20of%20the%20look%20or%20gaze%20of%20another%20and%20wanting%20to%20be%20esteemed%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%20came%20into%20being%20competition%20with%20others.%20Those%20who%20were%20more%20able%20and%20better%20started%20to%20command%20more%20respect%20and%20honours.%20This%20led%20to%20vanity%20and%20contempt%20in%20those%20so%20regarded%20and%20shame%20and%20envy%20in%20those%20less%20esteemed.%20This%20led%20to%20unhappiness%20and%20a%20fall%20from%20innocence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20an%20acute%20awareness%20of%20injustices%20meted%20out%20to%20one%2C%20and%20acts%20of%20revenge%20and%20cruelty%20are%20born.%20This%20in%20turn%20can%20lead%20to%20all%20sorts%20of%20social%20conflicts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20be%20aware%20that%20keeping%20up%20with%20the%20Joneses%20is%20not%20without%20its%20harmful%20consequences.%20If%20you%20avoid%20it%2C%20it%20may%20also%20be%20easier%20on%20your%20purse%2C%20because%20you%20can%20avoid%20wasteful%20conspicuous%20consumption.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20D.%20Samarender%20Reddy%20is%20co-founder%20%26amp%3B%20director%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F7qube.com%2F%5C%22%3E7Qube%20Biz%20Solutions.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690630246000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27203712%2FThe-Joneses.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fkeeping-up-with-the-joneses%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20are%20now%20always%20