0first%2C%20what%20is%20Disability%20Pride%20month%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22disability%20pride%20flag%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325551%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%20observed%20in%201990%2C%20Disability%20Pride%20Month%20commemorates%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20Americans%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%20on%20July%2026%2C%201990.%20Boston%20was%20among%20the%20first%20cities%20to%20mark%20the%20occasion%2C%20and%20the%20ripples%20of%20these%20celebrations%20are%20felt%20across%20the%20world%20today%2C%20in%20a%20powerful%20force%20of%20solidarity%20that%20has%20brought%20the%20community%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisability%20Pride%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20shed%20the%20traditional%20narratives%20of%20ableism%20and%20societal%20stigma%20that%20have%20surrounded%20the%20disability%20discourse%20for%20way%20too%20long%2C%20and%20view%20people%20with%20disabilities%20as%20equitable%20and%20positive%20contributors%20to%20society.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisability%20does%20not%20mean%20inability%2C%20and%20it%20is%20something%20that%20can%20happen%20to%20anyone%20anytime.%20There%E2%80%99s%20nothing%20upsetting%2C%20unfortunate%2C%20or%20inspiring%20about%20living%20the%20life%20of%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%20Disability%20Pride%20is%2C%20instead%2C%20a%20chance%20to%20look%20back%20on%20one%E2%80%99s%20journey%20to%20acknowledge%20how%20far%20they%20have%20come%2C%20the%20odds%20they%20have%20traversed%2C%20and%20how%20we%20may%20mobilise%20the%20community%2C%20garner%20support%2C%20and%20instil%20belief.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20%E2%80%98one%20size%20fits%20all%E2%80%99%20phenomenon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20one%E2%80%99s%20experience%20with%20disability%20is%20subjective%2C%20so%20is%20their%20understanding%20of%20Disability%20Pride%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20all%20about%20your%20lived%20experience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20young%20adult%2C%20%E2%80%98Disability%20Pride%E2%80%99%20seemed%20inauthentic%20and%20more%20of%20a%20propaganda%20campaign.%20I%20have%20faced%20so%20many%20challenges%20and%20lived%20so%20many%20awkward%20moments%20as%20a%20person%20with%20a%20locomotor%20disability.%20How%20could%20I%20be%20proud%20of%20my%20disability%3F%20But%20as%20I%20grew%20older%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20understanding%20what%20our%20disability%20is%20to%20us%2C%20being%20comfortable%20in%20our%20own%20skin%20and%20celebrating%20our%20journey%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Kavya%2C%20a%20job%20coach%20at%20v-shesh%2C%20an%20enterprise%20that%20prepares%20organisations%20with%20disability%20inclusion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Anjali%20Vyas%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F317421%2Fhow-to-build-inclusive-workplace-navigate-blood-disorders-thalassemia-with-employers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elives%20with%20an%20invisible%20disability%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20Multiple%20Sclerosis%2C%20%E2%80%9CDisability%20Pride%20has%20no%20visible%20boundaries.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Disability%20Pride%20Parade%20Chicago%20participants%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325555%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20disability%20pride%20parade%20in%20Chicago%20(Wikimedia%20Commons)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLiving%20with%20an%20invisible%20disability%20reminds%20me%20that%20strength%20and%20pride%20come%20in%20many%20forms.%20When%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20MS%2C%20things%20were%20definitely%20challenging%2C%20but%20in%20the%20face%20of%20that%20uncertainty%2C%20I%20found%20myself.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20I%20discovered%20my%20power.%20I%20am%20proud%20of%20the%20way%20I%20have%20been%20living%20with%20MS%20and%20defying%20limitations%20like%20the%20inaccessibility%2C%20ableism%20and%20the%20stigma%20around%20this%20invisible%20disability%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Anjali%2C%20a%20chemical%20engineer-turned-English%20language%20trainer%20from%20Bhandara%2C%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20this%20sense%20of%20pride%2C%20why%20is%20representation%20important%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20that%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20some%20earlier%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20in%20Indian%20cinema.%20How%20often%20have%20we%20seen%20that%20disability%20has%20been%20portrayed%20as%20a%20point%20of%20comic%20relief%2C%20or%20a%20punchline%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EGolmaal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2006)%2C%20Tusshar%20Kapoor%E2%80%99s%20character%20has%20a%20speech%20impairment%2C%20and%20Paresh%20Rawal%20and%20Sushmita%20Mukherjee%E2%80%99s%20characters%20are%20portrayed%20as%20blind%20%E2%80%94%20all%20for%20gags.%20In%20%3Cem%3EMujhse%20Shaadi%20Karogi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2004)%2C%20Kader%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20character%20is%20seen%20to%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdifferent%20disability%E2%80%9D%20every%20day.%20The%20staff%20at%20his%20care%20facility%20trivialises%20it%20and%20portrays%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmake-believe%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20character%20engages%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20in%20Indian%20films%20and%20other%20media%20leave%20a%20lot%20to%20be%20desired.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20say%20that%20these%20are%20just%20light-hearted%20movies%20meant%20for%20entertainment.%20But%20it%20is%20integral%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20we%20are%20at%20a%20point%20in%20history%20where%20there%20is%20a%20greater%20attempt%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20myths%20and%20stereotypes%2C%20and%20understand%20disability%20for%20what%20it%20truly%20is.%20Reducing%20it%20to%20a%20punchline%20reinforces%20existing%20stereotypes%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20viewers.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20popular%20trope%20that%20a%20number%20of%20filmmakers%20have%20engaged%20in%20is%20the%20infantilisation%20of%20people%20with%20disabilities.%20This%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20popular%20movies%20like%20%3Cem%3EKoi%20Mil%20Gaya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2003)%20and%20%3Cem%3EBarfi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2012).%20Here%2C%20adults%20with%20disabilities%20are%20portrayed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cinnocent%E2%80%9D%20or%20even%20childlike%20in%20their%20actions%2C%20speech%2C%20or%20capabilities.%20This%20contributes%20to%20the%20belief%20that%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20always%20need%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F253449%2Fcoronavirus-resources-for-persons-with-disabilities-caregivers-covid-19-online-support-groups-job-portals-companionship-mental-health-nimhans-india-div200%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20the%20care%20of%20someone%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20independent%2C%20the%20way%20one%20one%20would%20be%20with%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325558%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhile%20disability%20is%20caricaturized%20in%20Golmaal%2C%20Koi%20Mil%20Gayaa%20uses%20it%20to%20infantilize%20the%20main%20character.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20opposite%20route%20of%20morbidity.%20In%20%3Cem%3EGuzaarish%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2010)%2C%20we%20see%20Hrithik%20Roshan%E2%80%99s%20character%20insisting%20on%20how%20he%E2%80%99d%20rather%20die%20than%20live%20a%20long%20happy%20life%20as%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%20He%20has%20a%20promising%20career%2C%20and%20a%20supportive%20community.%20Yet%20he%20is%20unable%20to%20make%20meaning%20of%20his%20life.%20Persons%20who%20have%20acquired%20a%20disability%20go%20through%20a%20whole%20course%20of%20turbulent%20emotions%2C%20ones%20that%20may%20include%20the%20feelings%20described%20above.%20Films%20like%20this%20present%20a%20rather%20morbid%20take%20and%20make%20the%20viewer%20feel%20like%20this%20is%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20also%20often%20misses%20the%20mark%20is%20media%20representation%20of%20neurodiversity.%20Shows%20like%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Good%20Doctor%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3EAtypical%20%3C%2Fem%3Erepresent%20neurodiversity%20in%20stereotypical%20ways.%20For%20instance%2C%20not%20every%20individual%20who%20is%20on%20the%20autism%20spectrum%20possesses%20savant%20skills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20often%20goes%20untouched%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20autism%20is%20a%20spectrum%2C%20and%20that%20every%20autistic%20experience%20is%20unique%20and%20extremely%20individual-centric.%20Another%20bone%20of%20contention%20that%20affects%20the%20autistic%20community%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20such%20roles%20are%20played%20by%20allistic%20(non-autistic%20characters).%20Oftentimes%2C%20even%20the%20team%20of%20directors%20or%20writers%20is%20devoid%20of%20any%20person%20with%20autism%2C%20as%20was%20true%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Atypical%2C%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAtypical%2Fstatus%2F890667170266357760%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eautistic%20representation%20could%20only%20manage%20to%20find%20a%20place%20in%20one%20of%20the%20supporting%20roles%20and%20the%20social%20media%20team%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhere%20are%20the%20PwDs%20in%20the%20writers%E2%80%99%20rooms%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20make%20pity%20or%20sympathy%20the%20focal%20point%20of%20disability%20and%20take%20away%20from%20the%20narrative%20of%20pride%20and%20equity.%20A%20big%20reason%20why%20the%20representation%20of%20disability%20remains%20rudimentary%20is%20that%20there%20are%20very%20few%20PwDs%20in%20the%20writer%E2%80%99s%20rooms%2C%20wearing%20the%20director%E2%80%99s%20cap%2C%20or%20even%20representing%20themselves%20on%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20in%20the%20United%20States%20has%20shown%20that%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F07%2F28%2Farts%2Ftelevision%2Fdisability-representation-study-film-television.html%5C%22%3E95%25%20of%20the%20characters%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20played%20by%20actors%20without%20disabilities.%20In%20the%20USA%2C%20there%20is%20one%20person%20with%20a%20disability%20for%20every%20four%20people%2C%20but%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.respectability.org%2F2019%2F11%2Fglaad-tv-report-2019%2F%5C%22%3E3.1%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20characters%20that%20are%20shown%20on-screen%20are%20disabled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20are%20even%20lesser%20for%20children%20with%20disabilities%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fseejane.org%2Fresearch-informs-empowers%2Fsee-jane-2019%2F%5C%22%3Eless%20than%20one%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Several%20studies%20also%20show%20that%20the%20industry%20is%20losing%20billions%20of%20dollars%20by%20not%20being%20inclusive%20%E2%80%94%20the%20spirit%C2%A0%20of%20the%20DEI%20(Disability%20Equality%20Indiex)%20has%20not%20yet%20seeped%20into%20the%20creative%20space.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20research%20study%20by%20Ruderman%20Family%20Foundation%20found%20that%20Hollywood%20is%20incurring%20whopping%20losses%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frudermanfoundation.org%2Fwhite_papers%2Fdisability-inclusion-in-movies-and-television-market-research-2019%2F%5C%22%3E%24125%20billion%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20year%20by%20not%20having%20authentic%20disability%20representation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhere%20we%20make%20strides%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20disability%20representation%20in%20mainstream%20media%20is%20still%20far%20from%20authentic%2C%20it%20has%20come%20a%20long%20way%20from%20being%20restricted%20to%20characters%20that%20garner%20a%20few%20laughs%20to%20ones%20that%20foster%20compassion%20and%20are%20a%20window%20into%20the%20life%20of%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20list%20of%20a%20few%20recommendations%20that%20you%20can%20indulge%20in%20this%20Disability%20Pride%20Month%20with%20your%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMargarita%20with%20a%20Straw%20(2014)%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Based%20on%20the%20book%20%3Cem%3EOne%20Little%20Finger%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20movie%20features%20Laila%2C%20a%20young%20woman%20with%20Cerebral%20Palsy%2C%20who%20goes%20to%20New%20York%20to%20pursue%20her%20education%20and%20unfurls%20a%20new%20chapter%20of%20her%20life.%20The%20movie%20beautifully%20depicts%20the%20diverse%20crossroads%20one%20finds%20themselves%20at%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20friendships%20and%20relationships.%20(NC-17%20only%3A%20Not%20suitable%20for%20viewers%20under%2017%20years.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll%20data-origheight%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtu