he%20film%20in%20Raipur%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20these%20groups%20forced%20posters%20of%20the%20movie%20to%20be%20taken%20down%2C%20many%20prominent%20voices%20spoke%20up%20against%20this.%20One%20of%20them%20was%20former%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20Nayak%20later%20recalled%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20help%20came%20from%20two%20%E2%80%9Cprogressive%E2%80%9D%20politicians.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20told%20Indira%20Gandhi%20(then%20I%26amp%3BB%20Minister)%20also%20saw%20portions%20of%20the%20film%20and%20said%20the%20film%20promotes%20national%20integration.%20The%20protests%20died%20down%20after%20that.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crew%20powered%20through%20the%20backlash%20and%20managed%20to%20have%20the%20film%20premiere%20in%20April%201965.%20Ironically%2C%20the%20hullabaloo%20that%20the%20film%20created%20drew%20more%20attention%20with%20people%20flocking%20to%20cinema%20screens%20to%20catch%20it.%20It%20opened%20the%20windows%20for%20society%20to%20take%20cognisance%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F23061%2Fone-man-is-breaking-all-stereotypes-attached-with-indian-weddings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevils%20of%20the%20caste%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20film%20also%20served%20as%20the%20launchpad%20for%20Chhollywood%20(as%20the%20film%20industry%20of%20Chhattisgarh%20is%20popularly%20known)%20and%20was%20screened%20in%20Raipur%20in%202015%20at%20a%20film%20festival%20to%20mark%20the%20jubilee%20of%20this%20event.%20For%20Nayak%2C%20this%20event%20held%20tremendous%20significance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20196px)%20100vw%2C%20196px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-4-1689943596.jpg%5C%22%20